- Use `@nestjs/common` version 9.x for the latest features and improvements.
- Implement caching using `@nestjs/common/cache` module.
- Configure cache manager in `app.module.ts`:
  ```typescript
  import { CacheModule, Module } from '@nestjs/common';
  @Module({
    imports: [
      CacheModule.register({
        ttl: 60,
        max: 100,
      }),
    ],
  })
  export class AppModule {}
  ```
- Use `@CacheInterceptor` to cache responses:
  ```typescript
  import { Controller, Get } from '@nestjs/common';
  import { CacheInterceptor, UseInterceptors } from '@nestjs/common';

  @Controller('example')
  export class ExampleController {
    @Get()
    @UseInterceptors(CacheInterceptor)
    getExample() {
      return 'Cached data';
    }
  }
  ```
- For Redis caching, install `@nestjs-modules/ioredis`:
  ```bash
  npm install @nestjs-modules/ioredis --save
  ```
- Configure Redis in `app.module.ts`:
  ```typescript
  import { CacheModule } from '@nestjs/common';
  import { IORedisStore } from '@nestjs-modules/ioredis';

  @Module({
    imports: [
      CacheModule.register({
        store: IORedisStore,
        host: 'localhost',
        port: 6379,
      }),
    ],
  })
  export class AppModule {}
  ```
- Use `@RedisCacheInterceptor` for Redis caching:
  ```typescript
  import { Controller, Get } from '@nestjs/common';
  import { RedisCacheInterceptor, UseInterceptors } from '@nestjs-modules/ioredis';

  @Controller('example')
  export class ExampleController {
    @Get()
    @UseInterceptors(RedisCacheInterceptor)
    getExample() {
      return 'Redis cached data';
    }
  }
  ```
- Test caching strategies using NestJS testing utilities:
  ```bash
  npm run test:e2e
  ```
- Monitor cache performance and adjust TTL and max settings accordingly.
